Package: ozma-proxmox-plugin
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         qemu-system-x86,
         python3,
         python3-pil,
         python3-aiohttp,
         python3-gi,
         gir1.2-spiceclientglib-2.0,
         pve-qemu-kvm (>= 8.0),
         libpve-access-control,
         proxmox-ve (>= 8.0)
Recommends: looking-glass-client
Description: Ozma KVM integration for Proxmox VE
 Install once on each Proxmox node. Every VM becomes an ozma node
 automatically — display capture, input injection, audio routing,
 agent install, all managed from the Proxmox UI or the ozma dashboard.
 .
 Includes:
  - Ozma soft node (auto-created per VM, no manual setup)
  - QEMU KVMFR display backend (direct framebuffer, no VNC/SPICE)
  - D-Bus keyboard + mouse input injection
  - Looking Glass shared memory capture
  - Multi-head virtio-gpu (multiple monitors per VM)
  - Multi-channel PipeWire audio (5.1/7.1 surround)
  - GPU passthrough with IddCx virtual display
  - VM profiles (gaming/workstation/server/media) with auto-tuning
  - One-click Windows/Linux agent install into VMs
  - Proxmox web UI extension (Ozma tab per VM)
  - VM lifecycle hooks (start/stop/migrate/backup)
  - Auto-registration with ozma controller
